unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Cottonee
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.
unova_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Whimsicott with a Sun Stone.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Whimsicott
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: Like a puff of cotton, it can slip through cracks in walls. It appears wherever there are whirlwinds.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Petilil
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The leaves on its head are bitter, but they can be used to relieve fatigue.
unova_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Lilligant with a Sun Stone.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Lilligant
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The flower on its head gives off a relaxing fragrance, but it will wilt if neglected.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Basculin
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very hostile to each other. They are a rough, violent bunch.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Sandile
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Krokorok
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: They live in a pack of several individuals. The special membrane that covers their eyes can sense the heat of objects.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Krookodile
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Darumaka
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Darmanitan
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: When it gets injured in a battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Maractus
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Dwebble
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Crustle
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can Psik a heavy boulder with ease. It fights over territory with other Crustle.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Scraggy
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself. It is a ruffian that will attack anything that meets its gaze.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Scrafty
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the leader.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Sigilyph
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It was the guardian of cities in ancient times. It uses its psychic powers to attack foes that invade its territory.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Yamask
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Cofagrigus
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Tirtouga
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Carracosta
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can smash a tanker truck with a single slap. It is a very powerful and ferocious Pokémon.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Archen
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It is said to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon. It can't fly, so it lives in treetops.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Archeops
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can fly, but it is more adept at running. It is said to be able to outrun a car.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Trubbish
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused this Pokémon to be born.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Garbodor
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with a belch of poison gas.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Zorua
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. It often transforms into a silent child.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Zoroark
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can fool a crowd of people. It protects its lair with illusory scenery.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Minccino
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It uses its tail to clean its den. It is a very tidy Pokémon.
unova_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Cinccino with a Shiny Stone.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Cinccino
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: Its body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Gothita
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It stares at something only it can see. It is said that it can see the spirits of the dead.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Gothorita
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It uses hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. It is said that it can steal people away.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Gothitelle
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It can see the future from the movement of the stars. It can also see a Trainer's life span.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Solosis
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is enveloped in a special liquid.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Duosion
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It has two brains that are linked by a psychic power. It can cause its foe's head to ache.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Reuniclus
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It has magnificent intelligence. It can form a network with other Reuniclus by making their arms link together.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Ducklett
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a skilled diver. It can shoot a powerful jet of water from its mouth.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Swanna
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a graceful dancer. It is said that the leader of the flock is the one that can dance most gracefully.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Vanillite
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It was born from an icicle that was bathed in the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Vanillish
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It freezes particles of water in the air to make its body. It can survive in temperatures of 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Vanilluxe
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It swallows large amounts of water, then creates snow clouds inside its body.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Deerling
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. They hide from enemies by hiding in patches of grass.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Sawsbuck
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The plants on its horns change depending on the season. The leader of the herd is the one with the most splendid horns.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Emolga
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It glides on its cape-like membranes. It grills berries with electricity and eats them.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Karrablast
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. They are often targeted by Shelmet.
unova_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Escavalier when traded for a Shelmet.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Escavalier
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. They are bravely defiant.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Foongus
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Amoonguss
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: It lures prey close with its Poké Ball-like arms, then sprays them with poison spores.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Frillish
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Jellicent
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's territory: All sunken, all lost, all vanished.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Alomomola
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and use their special membrane to heal it.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Joltik
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Galvantula
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

unova_pokedex_part_2.name: Ferroseed
unova_pokedex_part_2.description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.
